  "notes": [
    "Wider ranged-repeat quantified-group boundary workloads keep captures, counted ranges, and haystacks intentionally tiny so the scorecard measures helper-call overhead for the newly supported bounded `{1,3}` slice rather than regex throughput.",
    "Measured rows cover the bounded `a(bc|de){1,3}d` and `a(?P<word>bc|de){1,3}d` compile/search/fullmatch paths directly at representative lower-bound, mixed-branch, and third-repetition haystacks, while still-wider counted ranges, open-ended repeats, conditional combinations, and broader backtracking-heavy grouped shapes stay as explicit known-gap rows until queued follow-on slices land."
  ],
